name: $resourceType
desc: Returns the FHIR type name for this instance

name: $identifier
desc: Returns: Identifier for the organization that is used to identify the endpoint across multiple disparate systems.

name: $addidentifier
desc: Identifier for the organization that is used to identify the endpoint across multiple disparate systems.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Identifier for the organization that is used to identify the endpoint across multiple disparate systems.

name: $status
desc: Returns: active | suspended | error | off | test.

name: $connectionType
desc: Returns: A coded value that represents the technical details of the usage of this endpoint, such as what WSDLs should be used in what way. (e.g. XDS.b/DICOM/cds-hook).

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: A coded value that represents the technical details of the usage of this endpoint, such as what WSDLs should be used in what way. (e.g. XDS.b/DICOM/cds-hook).

name: $::name
desc: Returns: A friendly name that this endpoint can be referred to with.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: A friendly name that this endpoint can be referred to with.

name: $managingOrganization
desc: Returns: The organization that manages this endpoint (even if technically another organisation is hosting this in the cloud, it is the organisation associated with the data).

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The organization that manages this endpoint (even if technically another organisation is hosting this in the cloud, it is the organisation associated with the data).

name: $contact
desc: Returns: Contact details for a human to contact about the subscription. The primary use of this for system administrator troubleshooting.

name: $addcontact
desc: Contact details for a human to contact about the subscription. The primary use of this for system administrator troubleshooting.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Contact details for a human to contact about the subscription. The primary use of this for system administrator troubleshooting.

name: $period
desc: Returns: The interval during which the endpoint is expected to be operational.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The interval during which the endpoint is expected to be operational.

name: $payloadType
desc: Returns: The payload type describes the acceptable content that can be communicated on the endpoint.

name: $addpayloadType
desc: The payload type describes the acceptable content that can be communicated on the endpoint.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: The payload type describes the acceptable content that can be communicated on the endpoint.

name: $payloadMimeType
desc: Returns: The mime type to send the payload in - e.g. application/fhir+xml, application/fhir+json. If the mime type is not specified, then the sender could send any content (including no content depending on the connectionType).

name: $addpayloadMimeType
desc: The mime type to send the payload in - e.g. application/fhir+xml, application/fhir+json. If the mime type is not specified, then the sender could send any content (including no content depending on the connectionType).

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The mime type to send the payload in - e.g. application/fhir+xml, application/fhir+json. If the mime type is not specified, then the sender could send any content (including no content depending on the connectionType).

name: $address
desc: Returns: The uri that describes the actual end-point to connect to.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The uri that describes the actual end-point to connect to.

name: $header
desc: Returns: Additional headers / information to send as part of the notification.

name: $addheader
desc: Additional headers / information to send as part of the notification.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Additional headers / information to send as part of the notification.
